videoSnippet.title: Student Meets Master! || Carlsen vs Van Foreest || FIDE World Rapid Championship (2022)
videoSnippet.description:
Abdusattorov vs Carlsen 2021 HERE! https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8d8bUgICOEw

Photos by Lenart Ootes
Have a great day :)

Carlsen, Magnus (2834) - Van Foreest, Jorden (2693)
FIDE World Rapid Championship (chess24.com) [6] 2022.12.27
A13 English opening

1.c4 e6 2.g3 d5 3.Bg2 d4 4.d3 c5 5.e3 Nf6 6.exd4 cxd4 7.a3 a5 8.Bg5 Nc6 9.Nd2 Be7 10.Ne2 O-O 11.O-O e5 12.Bxf6 Bxf6 13.Re1 h5 14.c5 Be7 15.Rc1 a4 16.Nc4 Be6 17.Bxc6 bxc6 18.Nxe5 Bg5 19.Nxc6 Qf6 20.f4 Bb3 21.Qd2 Qxc6 22.fxg5 Qd5 23.h4 Rac8 24.Nf4 Qd7 25.Re4 Rc6 26.Qf2 Rd8 27.Nxh5 Bd5 28.Rxd4 Qc8 29.Nf4 Rxc5 30.Rxc5 Qxc5 31.Nxd5 Rxd5 32.Rxd5 Qxd5 33.d4 Qe4 34.Qd2 Qf3 35.Kh2 Qd5 36.Qd1 Qb5 37.Qd2 Qd5 38.h5 Qf3 39.h6 Qh5+ 40.Kg2 Qg4 41.d5 Qe4+ 42.Kh2

00:00 Hello Everyone!
01:00 Game Starts!
01:45 Completely New Game!
08:00 It was In This Position!
10:10 Contributions!

The FIDE Women's World Rapid Championship is an 11-round Swiss tournament taking place from 26–28 December 2022 in Almaty, Kazakhstan. The prize fund is $150,000, with a $40,000 top prize.

Players receive 15 minutes for the entire game, plus a 10-second increment starting from move one. A tie for 1st is decided by two 3+2 blitz games. If still tied, more 3+2 games are played until a player wins. Official website: worldrapidandblitz2022.fide.com
